# 🗂️ Day 7 – Weekly Review & Mini Project

This project is part of the **30-Day DevOps Mastery Plan**.  
On Day 7, we focused on reviewing all foundational DevOps concepts learned during the first 6 days and applied them in a hands-on mini project.

---

## 📘 Topics Reviewed (Days 1–6)

| Day | Focus Area       |
|-----|------------------|
| 1   | DevOps Fundamentals & SDLC |
| 2   | Linux Basics & Commands    |
| 3   | Git Essentials              |
| 4   | Git Branching & Collaboration |
| 5   | Advanced Git & Shell Scripting |
| 6   | Shell Scripting Project     |

---

## ✅ Mini Project Overview

### 📄 Project: Git + Bash Automation

> Build a simple Git-powered automation script that:
> - Initializes a Git repo
> - Adds a README
> - Commits changes
> - Pushes to GitHub (via command line)
> - Logs output to a text file

---

## 🛠️ Tools Used

- **Git**
- **Bash**
- **GitHub CLI** (or Git remote)
- **Linux Terminal / WSL**

